{
  "stem": "24346.1",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I mentioned before-- from the organizations, the Jews belonged to organization-- my oldest brother, Jacob, belonged to a club, Jewish club.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It was called Bar Kokhba.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And he was a boxer.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "They had a soccer-playing club.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "They had a boxing club.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "They had different-- but he was a boxer.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And I remember, once, we went to our uncle on a Saturday to visit our uncle.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Now, it's that we're walking distance, but it took about an hour, because we couldn't ride the streetcar on Saturdays, so we walked there.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And somehow, if a Pole was drunk, he never fell on another Pole.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "He always fell on a religious Jew that he would recognize that was Jewish, always.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "So naturally, he fell on my mother when we walked.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "My oldest brother was there with us and told him, like, lay off.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "He didn't heed the warning.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "He fell on my father, too.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "So he grabbed him by the lapels.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "He gave him one punch, and he was let out.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And we continued on our way.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So that was the organization taught you like-- the Jewish organizations taught you a little self-defense.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Boxing.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "That was an incident.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And that just didn't happen to us.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "From what we heard, it happens to many people-- always happens to fall on a Jewish couple or a Jewish boy or a Jewish young man-- incidents like this.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And were you able to continue to do business at that time?",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes, yes.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Until the war broke out, we were able to do business, because a Jewish business like a kosher store, we had no Gentile clientele.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We had only customers who ate kosher food, so we had no problem regarding our business.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Business were done as usual.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "In September, the Germans invaded Poland.",
      "word_count": 6
    }
  ],
